rComments: Her lectures are so helpful. They are very well planned and detailed, and they make difficult theory accessible. She marks quickly and fairly. You can tell she wants all of her students to succeed and does what she can to make that happen.

The class centers on some really complex and intense theories, but she tries to make it as easy to digest and engage with as she can with both lecture material and with the order she assigns readings in. She tries to help students understand the theories and is more than happy to take extra time in and outside of class to help. VERY accommodating.
Her lectures are great. She goes into so much detail and throughly explains everything. Ive learned a lot about what to look for in a text.

I took her English class at York and shes very fair. You have to go to class and take notes she explains a lot and you have books to read. She gives a lot of advice to help make your paper/essay good and she will tell you what to do to make it better. If you want an easy English course take it with her
